"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1929428-2024-Olympics-Team-GB-gold-Tom-Pidcock\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Team GB cyclist Tom Pidcock was roundly jeered aftersealing Team GB's second gold medal of the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18, \"end\": 29, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 69, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999967343604683, \"rank\": 3.263673202781263e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a thrilling finale to the cross-country mountain bike race, Pidcock came into contact with Frenchman Victor Koretzky as he pulled off a thrilling overtaking manoeuvre at the end of the final lap.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 222, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the home crowd reacted angrily, booing Pidcock as he celebrated gold.\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not that the 24-year-old seemed bothered as he celebrated his dramatic win, after somehow overturning a 39-second deficit between him and Korentzky.\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While leading the race on the third lap, Pidcock suffered a puncture which looked to have scuppered his chances.\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he dug deep to mount a magnificent fightback, with British fans left angry at the lack of the respect from those in attendance.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9989423520799602, \"rank\": 0.0009472557619251896, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Unfortunately he was booed by the crowd at the finishing line, not good\\\" wrote @Liklesis on X.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The French spectators should have been more respectful, it's a shame they forgot themselves in the heat of the moment.\\\"\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7846814323251725, \"rank\": 0.26490429550668976, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1249, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999859028, \"rank\": 1.391269637232677e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"score\": 0.9997407757286504, \"rank\": 0.00025929138706482294, \"text\": \"Amazon Prime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  The crowd did at least remain respectful during the medal ceremony as God Save the King was played.\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Pidcock himself later defended his gold medal winning move, arguing he was entitled to attack the space his rival had left.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1888, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He left a gap and I had to go for it,\\\" he told theBBC.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But that's racing, some people might view it differently.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I want to show what sport is, not giving up.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a shame the French were booing me, but you know.\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2071, \"end\": 2077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7846814323251725, \"rank\": 0.26490429550668976, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that Victor was going to be super fast on the last lap, even if I could not get rid of him.\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"score\": 0.9158150400859676, \"rank\": 0.0916911135807484, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I knew it was going to be a big big fight.\\\"\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Brazilian swimmer issues emotional statement after being sent home from Olympics  Do not miss:Team GB hero 'wished she wasn't British' and fights back tears at Olympics 2024  Do not miss:What is in the cardboard boxes handed to Olympic medallists on podiums in Paris  He also admitted to feeling emotional after his win.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2363, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999967343604683, \"rank\": 3.263673202781263e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2530, \"end\": 2535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999859028, \"rank\": 1.391269637232677e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It wasn't easy,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am keeping my glasses on for a reason.\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think the Olympics is so special, you never give up and you have to give everything, that's what I had to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock's win signified a second gold medal in Paris for Team GB.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2819, \"end\": 2824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999859028, \"rank\": 1.391269637232677e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999967343604683, \"rank\": 3.263673202781263e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just hours earlier, the equestrian team of Laura Collett, Tom McEwen and Ros Cantertriumphed in the three-day eventing.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9997590961234223, \"rank\": 0.0002409613449882258, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 2881, \"end\": 2894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 2896, \"end\": 29